    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single gap (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is acknowledged and accepted on the basis that ASTM F1717 prescribes a single standard configuration and multi-condition testing is not feasible within the regulatory submission context. All quantitative validation metrics (E/uval < 1.96, percent difference < 10%) satisfied across both laboratories and all three primary QoIs. The FEA modeling framework is assessed as credible for the stated COU.",
